about.summary: Run VS Code on a remote server.

name: code-server
raw_recipe:
{% set name = "code-server" %}
{% set version = "3.9.3" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url: https://github.com/cdr/code-server/releases/download/v{{ version }}/code-server-{{ version }}-linux-amd64.tar.gz  # [linux64]
  sha256: eba42eaf868c2144795b1ac54929e3b252ae35403bf8553b3412a5ac4f365a41  # [linux64]
  url: https://github.com/cdr/code-server/releases/download/v{{ version }}/code-server-{{ version }}-linux-arm64.tar.gz  # [aarch64]
  sha256: 8a51d32b959af494846ce5b2111c06e3be5eb72bb087ba9bafc021323685e4fa  # [aarch64]
  url: https://github.com/cdr/code-server/releases/download/v{{ version }}/code-server-{{ version }}-macos-amd64.tar.gz  # [osx]
  sha256: 3f7ac66ae94918a15855992eb0676d76f17e0e7d0046220deabf4331c1470f12  # [osx]
  folder: code-server

build:
  number: 0
  binary_relocation: false  # [osx]
  skip: true  # [win]

requirements:
  host:
    - nodejs 12.*
  run:
    - nodejs 12.*

test:
  commands:
    - code-server --help

about:
  home: https://github.com/cdr/code-server
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file:
    - code-server/LICENSE.txt
    - code-server/ThirdPartyNotices.txt
  summary: Run VS Code on a remote server.

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - xhochy
    - jtilly
    - janjagusch

about.summary: Run VS Code on a remote server.
